---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Privacy Policy - Makonome" description="Makonome Privacy Policy">
  <main>
    <header>
      <a href="/" class="back-link">← Makonome</a>
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="meta">Last updated: February 17, 2026</p>
    </header>

    <article class="legal-content">

      <p>This Privacy Policy describes how Makonome ("we", "us", or "our") handles your information when you use the Makonome app ("App"). We are committed to protecting your privacy and being transparent about our practices.</p>

      <h2>1. Who We Are</h2>
      <p>Makonome is developed and maintained by Miro Čosić, based in Zagreb, Croatia.</p>
      <p><strong>Contact:</strong> <a href="mailto:metronome.app@gmail.com">metronome.app@gmail.com</a></p>

      <h2>2. Data We Collect</h2>

      <h3>2.1 Data Stored Locally on Your Device</h3>
      <p>The following data is stored exclusively on your device and is never transmitted to us or any third party:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Practice session history</strong> – dates, duration, BPM, time signature, and notes for each practice session you record</li>
        <li><strong>App usage time</strong> – total time you have spent using the App (used to display your practice stats)</li>
        <li><strong>App settings and preferences</strong> – your chosen sounds, BPM, time signature, subdivisions, themes, and presets</li>
        <li><strong>Trial and purchase status</strong> – whether your free trial is active and whether you have unlocked Makonome Pro</li>
      </ul>
      <p>This data is stored using Apple's standard local storage (UserDefaults) on your device. It is not backed up to our servers. If you delete the App, this data is permanently deleted.</p>

      <h3>2.2 Analytics Data (Amplitude)</h3>
      <p>We use <strong>Amplitude</strong> to collect anonymous, aggregated analytics data to understand how the App is used and to improve it. This may include:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>App opens and session duration</li>
        <li>Features used (e.g. which metronome controls are tapped)</li>
        <li>Device type, operating system version, and app version</li>
        <li>General geographic region (country level)</li>
        <li>Crash and error events</li>
      </ul>
      <p>This data does <strong>not</strong> include your name, email, practice session content, or precise location.</p>
      <p>Amplitude's privacy policy: <a href="https://amplitude.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">amplitude.com/privacy</a></p>

      <h3>2.3 In-App Purchases</h3>
      <p>In-App Purchases are processed entirely by <strong>Apple</strong> through the App Store. We do not collect or store your payment information. Apple's privacy policy applies to all payment processing: <a href="https://www.apple.com/legal/privacy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">apple.com/legal/privacy</a></p>

      <h3>2.4 Microphone (Tempo Detection)</h3>
      <p>If you use the <strong>Tempo Detection</strong> feature, the App will request access to your microphone. Audio is processed in real-time on your device solely to detect tempo. <strong>No audio is recorded, stored, or transmitted.</strong></p>

      <h2>3. How We Use Your Data</h2>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Data</th><th>Purpose</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Local practice data</td><td>Display your history and statistics within the App</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Usage time</td><td>Show your total practice time in the App</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Analytics (Amplitude)</td><td>Understand feature usage, fix bugs, improve the App</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Purchase status</td><td>Determine which features you have access to</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
      <p>We do not use your data for advertising, profiling, or selling to third parties.</p>

      <h2>4. Data Sharing</h2>
      <p>We do not sell, rent, or share your personal data with third parties, except:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Amplitude</strong> – anonymous analytics as described above</li>
        <li><strong>Apple</strong> – in-app purchase processing</li>
        <li><strong>Legal requirements</strong> – if required by law or to protect our legal rights</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>5. Your Rights (GDPR)</h2>
      <p>If you are located in the European Economic Area (EEA), you have the following rights under the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR):</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Right of access</strong> – request a copy of data we hold about you</li>
        <li><strong>Right to rectification</strong> – request correction of inaccurate data</li>
        <li><strong>Right to erasure</strong> – request deletion of your data</li>
        <li><strong>Right to data portability</strong> – request your data in a portable format</li>
        <li><strong>Right to object</strong> – object to certain types of processing</li>
        <li><strong>Right to withdraw consent</strong> – withdraw consent at any time</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Since most data is stored locally on your device, you can exercise many of these rights directly by clearing app data or deleting the App. For analytics data, contact us at <a href="mailto:metronome.app@gmail.com">metronome.app@gmail.com</a>.</p>
      <p><strong>Legal basis for processing:</strong> We process analytics data based on our legitimate interest in improving the App. You may opt out by contacting us.</p>

      <h2>6. Data Retention</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Local data:</strong> Retained on your device until you delete the App or clear its data</li>
        <li><strong>Analytics data:</strong> Retained by Amplitude per their data retention policy (up to 2 years by default)</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>7. Children's Privacy</h2>
      <p>The App is not directed at children under 13 years of age. We do not knowingly collect personal data from children under 13. If you believe a child has provided us with personal data, please contact us at <a href="mailto:metronome.app@gmail.com">metronome.app@gmail.com</a>.</p>

      <h2>8. Data Security</h2>
      <p>Local data is protected by your device's built-in security (encryption, passcode/Face ID). Analytics data is transmitted to Amplitude over encrypted connections (HTTPS).</p>

      <h2>9. Future Features</h2>
      <p>We may introduce new features (such as AI-powered coaching) that involve cloud processing. If this occurs, we will update this Privacy Policy and notify you before any changes take effect.</p>

      <h2>10. Changes to This Policy</h2>
      <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of significant changes by updating the "Last updated" date and, where appropriate, through an in-app notice.</p>

      <h2>11. Contact Us</h2>
      <p>If you have questions, concerns, or requests regarding this Privacy Policy:</p>
      <p><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:metronome.app@gmail.com">metronome.app@gmail.com</a></p>
      <p>We will respond within 30 days, as required by GDPR.</p>

      <p class="governing-law">This Privacy Policy is governed by the laws of the Republic of Croatia and applicable EU regulations, including the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR).</p>

    </article>

    <footer>
      <p>&copy; 2025 Makonome. Built with ♥ for musicians.</p>
      <nav>
        <a href="/manual">Manual</a>
        <a href="/changelog">Changelog</a>
        <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>
        <a href="/terms">Terms of Service</a>
      </nav>
    </footer>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>

